trans-unit.source: Removes the duplicate rows from a dataset
trans-unit.target: Removes the duplicate rows from a dataset

trans-unit.source: You can use the <ui>Remove Duplicate Rows</ui> module to remove all duplicate rows from the input data set based on the list of features (columns) you specify.
trans-unit.target: You can use the <ui>Remove Duplicate Rows</ui> module to remove all duplicate rows from the input data set based on the list of features (columns) you specify.

trans-unit.source: Two rows are considered duplicates if the values of all specified features are equal.
trans-unit.target: Two rows are considered duplicates if the values of all specified features are equal.

trans-unit.source: If the dataset has missing values, some additional conditions apply:
trans-unit.target: If the dataset has missing values, some additional conditions apply:

trans-unit.source: The input dataset is allowed to have missing values in key and non-key columns.
trans-unit.target: The input dataset is allowed to have missing values in key and non-key columns.

trans-unit.source: For key columns, a missing value is considered equal to other missing values, but not equal to non-missing values.
trans-unit.target: For key columns, a missing value is considered equal to other missing values, but not equal to non-missing values.

trans-unit.source: An exception is made when values are missing in key columns in sparse datasets.
trans-unit.target: An exception is made when values are missing in key columns in sparse datasets.

trans-unit.source: In a sparse dataset, the missing value is considered equal only if it equals the default representation of a sparse value.
trans-unit.target: In a sparse dataset, the missing value is considered equal only if it equals the default representation of a sparse value.

trans-unit.source: In the <externalLink><linkText>Breast cancer detection</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=525726</linkUri></externalLink> sample, <ui>Remove Duplicate Rows</ui> is used to consolidate the training and test datasets after adding feature columns
trans-unit.target: In the <externalLink><linkText>Breast cancer detection</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=525726</linkUri></externalLink> sample, <ui>Remove Duplicate Rows</ui> is used to consolidate the training and test datasets after adding feature columns

trans-unit.source: The <externalLink><linkText>Movie recommendation</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=525276</linkUri></externalLink> sample uses <ui>Remove Duplicate Rows</ui> to sanitize the data and ensure that there is only one user rating per movie.
trans-unit.target: The <externalLink><linkText>Movie recommendation</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=525276</linkUri></externalLink> sample uses <ui>Remove Duplicate Rows</ui> to sanitize the data and ensure that there is only one user rating per movie.

trans-unit.source: In the <externalLink><linkText>Twitter sentiment analysis</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=525274</linkUri></externalLink> sample, <ui>Remove Duplicate Rows</ui> is applied to only the ID and popularity columns, to ensure that there is only one ranking value per movie.
trans-unit.target: In the <externalLink><linkText>Twitter sentiment analysis</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=525274</linkUri></externalLink> sample, <ui>Remove Duplicate Rows</ui> is applied to only the ID and popularity columns, to ensure that there is only one ranking value per movie.

trans-unit.source: The module works by looping through all rows of the input dataset.
trans-unit.target: The module works by looping through all rows of the input dataset.

trans-unit.source: It collects into a candidate output dataset all rows where the unique combination of key column values appeared for the first time.
trans-unit.target: It collects into a candidate output dataset all rows where the unique combination of key column values appeared for the first time.

trans-unit.source: The input dataset is allowed to have missing values in non-key columns and key columns.
trans-unit.target: The input dataset is allowed to have missing values in non-key columns and key columns.

trans-unit.source: In key columns, a missing value is considered equal to other missing values, but not equal to non-missing values.
trans-unit.target: In key columns, a missing value is considered equal to other missing values, but not equal to non-missing values.

trans-unit.source: The column array type is preserved independently of the results of row filtering.
trans-unit.target: The column array type is preserved independently of the results of row filtering.

trans-unit.source: You cannot force the array to a particular data type by filtering out invalid values; the column array type is based on all values in the column.
trans-unit.target: You cannot force the array to a particular data type by filtering out invalid values; the column array type is based on all values in the column.

trans-unit.source: This restriction also applies when filtering missing values.
trans-unit.target: This restriction also applies when filtering missing values.

trans-unit.source: The algorithm used for comparing data values is hash-forced.
trans-unit.target: The algorithm used for comparing data values is hash-forced.

trans-unit.source: Choose the key columns to use when searching for duplicates.
trans-unit.target: Choose the key columns to use when searching for duplicates.

trans-unit.source: Indicate whether to keep the first row of a set of duplicates and discard others.
trans-unit.target: Indicate whether to keep the first row of a set of duplicates and discard others.

trans-unit.source: If False, the last duplicate row encountered is kept.
trans-unit.target: If False, the last duplicate row encountered is kept.
